{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"tarry-creep-range","description":"RISK 1 (cross-session duplication) + client reliability. Two competing prompt-authoring WRITE backends both wired into the editor: `prompt_authoring.save_prompt` (atomic temp-file + `os.replace`) and `prompt_library.create_prompt` (NON-atomic `path.write_text`, `prompt_library.py:240`). They write the same `.rebar/prompts/<id>.md` with divergent semantics — one atomic, one a latent half-write on crash; one rejects uppercase ids, the other accepts them.\n\n## Why\n`prompt_library` was added as an \"additive\" layer without folding in the pre-existing atomic writer two directories away. The editor exposes BOTH `/prompt/save` and `/library/create` POST endpoints (`src/rebar/llm/workflow/editor.py`), so a client can corrupt a prompt file via the non-atomic path. `create_prompt` is essentially a strict subset of `save_prompt` minus the atomicity + id-rule guarantees.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/llm/prompt_library.py:236-245` — make `create_prompt`/`_write` DELEGATE to `prompt_authoring.save_prompt` (project-forced target) instead of `path.write_text`.\n- Pick ONE id rule (prefer `prompt_authoring._valid_id`); reconcile `PromptExistsError` vs `PromptWriteError` semantics.\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/editor.py` — route `/library/create` through the atomic writer.\nKeep the `enumerate_library`/criterion-kind classification that `prompt_library` legitimately adds (only the WRITE path is duplicated, not the enumerate path).\n\n## Scope\nIn: one atomic write path, one id rule, shared error semantics. Out: the enumerate/classification surface (keep), the prompt schema/front-matter format.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All prompt writes (both editor endpoints) go through the atomic `os.replace` writer — no `write_text` write path remains.\n- [ ] A single id-validation rule governs both endpoints (documented).\n- [ ] A crash/interrupt mid-write cannot leave a partially-written `.rebar/prompts/<id>.md` (test via a write that fails before replace).\n- [ ] Existing prompt-authoring + library tests pass; `enumerate_library` behavior unchanged.","id":"c38b-98c3-b5cc-410c","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":1,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Risk 1: consolidate the two prompt-authoring write backends"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605237804960001,"uuid":"fc7be5ce-177b-4477-9711-c0d45656c8d8"}